str2: The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
All, the whole, altogether. Absolutely all or every one.
A multitude, crowd, great number, assemblage. From pletho; a fulness, i.e. A large number, throng, populace.

str2: To raise up, set up; I rise from among (the) dead; I arise, appear. From ana and histemi; to stand up.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: A primary verb; properly, to lead; by implication, to bring, drive, go, pass, or induce.

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
On, to, against, on the basis of, at.
Pilate. Of Latin origin; close-pressed, i.e. Firm; Pilatus, a Roman.
